<div class="c300_47">
<div id="v300.47.1"><span class="H1697 s">The word</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span><span class="H3414 s"> that came to Jeremiah</span><span class="H5030 s"> the prophet</span><span class="H6430 s"> against the Philistines</span><span class="H6547 s">, before that Pharaoh</span><span class="H5221 s"> smote</span><span class="H5804 s"> Gaza</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Gaza: Heb. Azzah)</span></div>
<div id="v300.47.2"><span class="H559 s">Thus saith</span><span class="H3068 s"> the LORD</span><span class="H4325 s">; Behold, waters</span><span class="H5927 s"> rise up</span><span class="H6828 s"> out of the north</span><span class="H7857 s">, and shall be an overflowing</span><span class="H5158 s"> flood</span><span class="H7857 s">, and shall overflow</span><span class="H776 s"> the land</span><span class="H4393 s">, and all that is therein</span><span class="H5892 s">; the city</span><span class="H3427 s">, and them that dwell</span><span class="H120 s"> therein: then the men</span><span class="H2199 s"> shall cry</span><span class="H3427 s">, and all the inhabitants</span><span class="H776 s"> of the land</span><span class="H3213 s"> shall howl</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (all that…: Heb. the fulness thereof)</span></div>
<div id="v300.47.3"><span class="H6963 s">At the noise</span><span class="H8161 s"> of the stamping</span><span class="H6541 s"> of the hoofs</span><span class="H47 s"> of his strong</span><span class="H7494 s"> <i>horses</i>, at the rushing</span><span class="H7393 s"> of his chariots</span><span class="H1995 s">, <i>and at</i> the rumbling</span><span class="H1534 s"> of his wheels</span><span class="H1 s">, the fathers</span><span class="H6437 s"> shall not look back</span><span class="H1121 s"> to <i>their</i> children</span><span class="H7510 s"> for feebleness</span><span class="H3027 s"> of hands</span>;</div>
<div id="v300.47.4"><span class="H3117 s">Because of the day</span><span class="H935 s"> that cometh</span><span class="H7703 s"> to spoil</span><span class="H6430 s"> all the Philistines</span><span class="H3772 s">, <i>and</i> to cut off</span><span class="H6865 s"> from Tyrus</span><span class="H6721 s"> and Zidon</span><span class="H5826 s"> every helper</span><span class="H8300 s"> that remaineth</span><span class="H3068 s">: for the LORD</span><span class="H7703 s"> will spoil</span><span class="H6430 s"> the Philistines</span><span class="H7611 s">, the remnant</span><span class="H339 s"> of the country</span><span class="H3731 s"> of Caphtor</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (the country: Heb. the isle)</span></div>
<div id="v300.47.5"><span class="H7144 s">Baldness</span><span class="H935 s"> is come</span><span class="H5804 s"> upon Gaza</span><span class="H831 s">; Ashkelon</span><span class="H1820 s"> is cut off</span><span class="H7611 s"> <i>with</i> the remnant</span><span class="H6010 s"> of their valley</span><span class="H1413 s">: how long wilt thou cut</span> thyself?</div>
<div id="v300.47.6"><span class="H1945 s">O</span><span class="H2719 s"> thou sword</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span><span class="H3808 s">, how long <i>will it be</i> ere</span><span class="H8252 s"> thou be quiet</span><span class="H622 s">? put up</span><span class="H8593 s"> thyself into thy scabbard</span><span class="H7280 s">, rest</span><span class="H1826 s">, and be still</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (put…: Heb. gather thyself)</span></div>
<div id="v300.47.7"><span class="H8252 s">How can it be quiet</span><span class="H3068 s">, seeing the LORD</span><span class="H6680 s"> hath given it a charge</span><span class="H831 s"> against Ashkelon</span><span class="H3220 s">, and against the sea</span><span class="H2348 s"> shore</span><span class="H3259 s">? there hath he appointed</span> it. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (How…: Heb. How canst thou)</span></div></div>
